üìò WEEK 2 ‚Äì DAY 6 JavaScript | Introduction
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üåê What is JavaScript?

**JavaScript (JS)** is a **programming language** used to make **web pages interactive and dynamic**.

* Runs in the browser
* Works with HTML & CSS
* Adds logic and behavior to websites

üìå HTML ‚Üí Structure
üìå CSS ‚Üí Style
üìå JavaScript ‚Üí Logic & interaction

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üöÄ Why JavaScript is Important

* Makes websites interactive
* Handles user actions (click, input)
* Validates forms
* Updates content without reloading
* Core skill for frontend & full stack developers

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß† What Can JavaScript Do?

* Show alerts
* Change HTML content
* Change styles
* Validate forms
* Fetch data from servers
* Build full applications

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚öôÔ∏è Ways to Use JavaScript

1Ô∏è‚É£ Inline JavaScript

```html
<button onclick="alert('Hello JS')">Click</button>
```

‚ùå Not recommended for large projects

---

2Ô∏è‚É£ Internal JavaScript

```html
<script>
  alert("Hello JavaScript");
</script>
```

---

3Ô∏è‚É£ External JavaScript (Best Practice)

```html
<script src="script.js"></script>
```

‚úî Clean
‚úî Reusable
‚úî Scalable

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üßæ First JavaScript Program

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
  <h1>Hello JavaScript</h1>

  <script>
    console.log("Hello World");
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

üìå Output appears in **browser console**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üñ•Ô∏è JavaScript Console

Used for **debugging and testing**.

```js
console.log("This is console output");
```

üìå Open with:

* Right click ‚Üí Inspect ‚Üí Console

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üì¶ Variables in JavaScript

Variables store data.

```js
let name = "Saakshi";
const age = 21;
var city = "Delhi";
```

Variable Keywords

| Keyword | Use            |
| ------- | -------------- |
| `let`   | Changeable     |
| `const` | Constant value |
| `var`   | Old (avoid)    |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üî¢ Data Types

```js
let number = 10;        // Number
let text = "Hello";    // String
let isTrue = true;     // Boolean
let value = null;      // Null
let x;                 // Undefined
```

---

‚ûï Operators

Arithmetic Operators

```js
+  -  *  /  %
```

Comparison Operators

```js
==   ===   !=   >   <
```

üìå `===` checks **value + type**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÄ Conditional Statements

if-else

```js
let age = 18;

if (age >= 18) {
  console.log("Adult");
} else {
  console.log("Minor");
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üîÅ Loops

for loop

```js
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

while loop

```js
let i = 1;
while (i <= 3) {
  console.log(i);
  i++;
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üß© Functions

Functions are reusable blocks of code.

```js
function greet() {
  console.log("Hello User");
}

greet();
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üñ±Ô∏è JavaScript Events

Events happen when users interact.

```html
<button onclick="show()">Click Me</button>

<script>
  function show() {
    alert("Button Clicked");
  }
</script>
```

Common events:

* `onclick`
* `onchange`
* `onmouseover`
* `onkeydown`

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üå≥ Introduction to DOM

**DOM (Document Object Model)** allows JavaScript to interact with HTML.

```js
document.getElementById("title").innerHTML = "Hello JS";
```

üìå JS can:

* Read HTML
* Change HTML
* Change CSS

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚ùå Common Beginner Mistakes

* Forgetting semicolons
* Using `var`
* Writing JS outside `<script>`
* Not checking console errors

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

üí° Best Practices

* Use external JS files
* Use `let` and `const`
* Write clean & readable code
* Use console for debugging

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

‚úÖ DAY-6 Summary (Week-2)

* What JavaScript is
* Ways to use JavaScript
* Variables & data types
* Conditions & loops
* Functions & events
* Intro to DOM
